    "## The main goal is to demonstrate sensitivity of eq.38 from\n",
    "## ref.: Allen R.G., Trezza R., Tasumi, Masahiro. Analytical integrated functions for daily solar radiation on slopes.\n",
    "## // Agricultural and Forest Meteorology 139 (2006) 55â€“73"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Importing all necessary classes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 65,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "from shyft import api\n",
    "from shyft.time_series import (Calendar,deltahours,UtcPeriod,TimeSeries,TimeAxis,DoubleVector,point_interpretation_policy)\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Importing camels data \n",
    "# (The data is prepared by Felix Matt for shyft-intorduction-course at Master's level at UiO Geohyd)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 66,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from camels_reader import TestData"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 67,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data = TestData()\n",
    "time_vec = api.UtcTimeVector(data.time)\n",
    "time_end = time_vec[-1] + 60*60*24\n",
    "ta = api.TimeAxisByPoints(time_vec, t_end=time_end)\n",
    "station_info, df = data._get_met_data_from_camels_database()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 68,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Radiaiton runner helps to run and plot radiaiton routine results\n",
    "from radiation_runner import RadiationRunner\n",
    "runner = RadiationRunner()\n",
    "def plot_results(xvar, yvar, fig1, ax1, ymax, xname, yname, plotname, lab, col, labloc, ymin=0.0):\n",
    "    \"\"\" Plots things\"\"\"\n",
    "    ax1.plot(xvar, yvar, col, label=lab)\n",
    "    ax1.set_ylabel(yname)\n",
    "    ax1.set_xlabel(xname)\n",
    "    plt.title(plotname)\n",
    "    plt.legend(loc=labloc, bbox_to_anchor=(1,0.5))\n",
    "    plt.axis([0, 365, ymin, int(ymax * 1.01)])\n",
    "    plt.grid(True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 69,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x504 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# This is result of calculation from pure camels data, assuming that radiation is measured on horizontal surface\n",
    "#\n",
    "latitude_deg = station_info['lat']\n",
    "slope_deg = 0.0\n",
    "aspect_deg = 0.0\n",
    "elevation= station_info['z']\n",
    "albedo = 0.5\n",
    "turbidity = 0.5\n",
    "ymax = 850\n",
    "yname = 'Rso, [W/m^2]'\n",
    "xname = 'DOY'\n",
    "plotname = \"Camels data 06191500 from shyft-intro-course\"\n",
    "labels = ('Ra','Rso')\n",
    "colors = ('r--','r', 'b--','b','g--','g','k--','k','m--','m')\n",
    "labloc = (\"upper left\",\"lower center\", \"upper center\",\"center left\")\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set(font_scale=1.8)\n",
    "fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 7))\n",
    "\n",
    "result = runner.run_radiation_ta(ta,latitude_deg, slope_deg, aspect_deg, elevation, albedo, turbidity, data.temperature, data.relative_humidity, '24-hour', data.radiation)\n",
    "ax1.plot(data.radiation, label='from-source')\n",
    "plot_results(result[0], result[2], fig1, ax1, ymax, xname, yname, plotname, 'from-model-predicted-clear-sky', colors[0],labloc[1])\n",
    "plot_results(result[0], result[3], fig1, ax1, ymax, xname, yname, plotname, 'from-model-translated', colors[4],labloc[1])"
   ]
  },

    "#### The other notebook (radiation_sensitivity) shows only clear-sky radiation behavior\n",
    "# Now lets play around with aspect, slope, albedo, turbidity \n",
    "fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 5))\n",
    "slope_array = [0.0, 30.0, 45.0, 60.0, 75.0, 90.0, 110, 180, 190]\n",
    "aspect_deg = 0.0\n",
    "plotname = \"Camels data 06191500 slope variation\"\n",
    "i = 0\n",
    "for slope_deg in slope_array:\n",
    "    result = runner.run_radiation_ta(ta,latitude_deg, slope_deg, aspect_deg, elevation, albedo, turbidity, data.temperature, data.relative_humidity, '24-hour', data.radiation)\n",
    "    plot_results(result[0], result[3], fig1, ax1, ymax, xname, yname, plotname, str(slope_deg), colors[i],labloc[3])\n",
    "    i+=1"

    "fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 5))\n",
    "turbidity_array = 0.5\n",
    "slope_deg = 0.0 # if slope is 0 no aspect impact could be seen\n",
    "aspect_deg = 0.0\n",
    "albedo = 0.5\n",
    "temp_plus10 = np.array([c+10 for c in data.temperature])\n",
    "temp_minus10 = np.array([c-10 for c in data.temperature])\n",
    "latitude_deg = station_info['lat']\n",
    "i = 0\n",
    "plotname = \"Camels data 06191500 temperature variation\"\n",
    "result = runner.run_radiation_ta(ta,latitude_deg, slope_deg, aspect_deg, elevation, albedo, turbidity, data.temperature, data.relative_humidity, '24-hour', data.radiation)\n",
    "result1 = runner.run_radiation_ta(ta,latitude_deg, slope_deg, aspect_deg, elevation, albedo, turbidity, temp_plus10, data.relative_humidity, '24-hour', data.radiation)\n",
    "result2 = runner.run_radiation_ta(ta,latitude_deg, slope_deg, aspect_deg, elevation, albedo, turbidity, temp_minus10, data.relative_humidity, '24-hour', data.radiation)\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_results(result[0], result[2], fig1, ax1, ymax, xname, yname, plotname, 'original', colors[0],labloc[3])\n",
    "plot_results(result1[0], result1[2], fig1, ax1, ymax, xname, yname, plotname, 't+10', colors[2],labloc[3])\n",
    "plot_results(result2[0], result2[2], fig1, ax1, ymax, xname, yname, plotname, 't-10', colors[4],labloc[3])\n",
    "\n"
   ]
